                            <comment id="13238671" author="jim.manico@owasp.org" created="Mon, 26 Mar 2012 18:50:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just a polite note, Session Id&apos;s in URL&apos;s are a serious vulnerability &lt;br/&gt;
(session rewriting). In general, GET request parameters should never &lt;br/&gt;
contain sensitive data since they leak (bookmarks, proxy/web server &lt;br/&gt;
logs, referrer headers, etc).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Forgive me if this is already known or inappropriate. I&apos;m new here. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Aloha,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211; &lt;br/&gt;
Jim Manico&lt;/p&gt;

